nty-first century. Landry investigates the educational and occupational attainment, income and wealth, methods of child-rearing, community-building priorities, and residential settlement patterns of this growing yet still-understudied segment of the U.S. population.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aAfrican AmericansxEconomic conditionsy21st century. 0aMiddle class African AmericansxSocial conditionsy21st century. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aAfrican American.  aAmerican.  aCommunity.  aPrince George’s County, Maryland.  ablack.  aclass.  acollege education.  aculture.  adesegregation.  adiscrimination.  aeducational attainment.  ahistorically black colleges and universities.  aincome inequality.  aincome.  aintegration.  amiddle class.  aneighborhoods.  anew black middle class.  aoccupational attainment.  arace.  aregregation.  aresidential location.  asocial.  asociology.  asuburbanization.  aupper middle class.  awealth.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311066608340uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978081359400240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813594002423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780813594002.jpg  a978-3-11-066608-3  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK